Maltego
Visual link analysis tool for OSINT

Information Gathering
Description
Maltego is a powerful OSINT and graphical link analysis tool. It maps relationships between pieces of information gathered from the internet, helping visualize connections between entities.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which maltego
Install command:

sudo apt install maltego
Basic Syntax
maltego (GUI application)
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
maltego

Launch Maltego	Starting OSINT investigation	
Add entity: Domain

Start with a domain	Beginning domain investigation	
Run transform: To DNS Name

Find DNS records	Discovering subdomains	
Run transform: To Email Addresses

Find related emails	Email harvesting	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Launch Maltego and create new graph
2
Add starting entity (domain, email, person)
3
Right-click and run transforms
4
Explore relationships visually
5
Export findings for reporting
Understanding the Output
Visual graph shows entities as nodes and relationships as edges. Different colors indicate entity types.

Important Warnings
•
Community Edition has limitations
•
Some transforms use external APIs
•
OSINT is generally legal but respect privacy
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
